snippet.title: i9 9900K Hackintosh for Developers - 3x Compile Speed
snippet.description:
Hackintoshes are popular since you can configure them with very powerful components at a relatively low price point. In today's video, I'll go over all of the internal parts for my current build.  I've been using this machine for the past year for all my professional work and its been an absolutely beast running Catalina.

i9 9900K CPU: https://amzn.to/2PaXB5b
ASUS TUF z390 mATX Motherboard: https://amzn.to/2P99etr
32GB Corsair Vengeance RGB RAM: https://amzn.to/387eR3R
32GB GSkill RAM: https://amzn.to/2YeCm6v
Radeon RX570 Graphics Card: https://amzn.to/33NcNe6
Intel 660P m.2 SSD: https://amzn.to/34Jvwse
Corsair Crystal Series 280x RGB: https://amzn.to/2P6qf7y
Corsair H100i AIO Liquid Cooler: https://amzn.to/34PWsqu
Broadcom Wifi & Bluetooh Adapter on Ebay
